Outline of this application
-A web application for coworking space management and reservation.
-Admin: Managing spaces, users, spaces' amenities, reservations, reviews, contacts, and notification.
-User: Search for spaces, book a space, cancel a reservation, post a review, creae a contact.

Used technologies
-Laravel＠11.46.1
-Vue@3.5.30

This project is designed as an MVP, focusing on core functionality with room for scalability and improvement.

## Challenges & Improvement Points

### 🧠 Design / Logic
- Prevent overlapping reservations for the same space and time
  → Needs stronger backend control (e.g. transaction / locking)

- Clarify reservation lifecycle when payment is introduced
  → Decide whether reservation is confirmed before or after payment

- Simplify backend validation logic
  → Reduce duplicated condition checks in controllers

---

### ⚙️ Backend
- Replace `fill()` + `save()` with `update()` where appropriate
- Refactor sorting functions (argument consistency using Builder)
- Improve filtering logic (handling 'all' values more cleanly)
- Simplify route definitions using prefix and name grouping

---

### 🎨 Frontend / UX
- Separate filtering and sorting UI for better usability
- Maintain filter state when sorting is changed
- Add rows-per-page selection for index pages (reservations, spaces, reviews)
- Improve admin messages (auto-dismiss or manually dismissible)
- Adjust UI details (e.g. spacing between review stars, layout consistency)

---

### 🧹 Code Quality
- Unify naming conventions (camelCase)
- Remove unused files and clean project structure
- Add comments for better readability and maintainability
- Refactor common utility functions (e.g. formatPrice, formatTime)

